A corps member serving in Mararaba, Nasarawa State, is lucky to be alive after being butchered by some robbers trying to snatch his phone.

Omoregbe Hossana, a graduate of Houdegbe North American University, had stepped out, last night, to give direction to someone, when the hoodlums attacked him with cutlasses, while demanding for his phone.
However, he was rescued by a security guard who intervened but also ended up being macheted by the suspects. The duo were later rushed to the Maraba Medical Centre, where they are currently recuperating.
According to his fellow corpers in the state, they are constantly living fear of being attacked by vicious robbers terrorizing the area.
